- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a new method for learning graphs using NetGAN.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of random walks to generate graphs, which is a common technique in data structures and algorithms.
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a new method for improving the performance of NetGAN, which is a software tool for generating graphs.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for generating graphs.
